<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta content='text/html; charset=UTF-8' http-equiv='Content-Type' />
  </head>
  <body>
    
    <table>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td style="vertical-align: top;">
            <%= link_to image_tag(group_badge_url(@group, @badge, format: :png), size: "100x100", \
              alt: @badge.name), group_badge_url(@group, @badge) %>
          </td>
          <td style="padding: 10px; vertical-align: top;">
            
            <% if @to_creator %>
            
              <p>
                You have created a new badge in the <%= link_to @group.name, group_url(@group) %> learning group. 
                You have automatically been added as an expert of the <%= @badge.name %> badge.
                Being a badge expert allows you to issue the badge and help guide badge learners.
              </p>
              <p>
                If you wish, you can now add this badge to your Mozilla Open Badges Backpack by visiting 
                your user profile in Badge List.
              </p>

            <% else %>
            
              <p>
                You have been awarded the <%= link_to @badge.name, group_badge_url(@group, @badge) %> badge in 
                Badge List. You are now one of the badge experts, congratulations! Being a badge expert 
                allows you to issue the badge and help guide badge learners.
              </p>
              <p>
                If you wish, you can now add this badge to your Mozilla Open Badges Backpack by visiting 
                your user profile in Badge List. Also be aware that all non-private entries in your progress 
                log are now visible and will be linked to the badge as public evidence of your achievment. 
                (You can change the visibility of your progress log at any time by altering the visibility 
                options in Badge List.)
              </p>
            
            <% end %>

          </td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <hr/>

    <p>
      <strong>Your Badge Progress Log:</strong> 
      <%= link_to group_badge_log_url(@group, @badge, @log), group_badge_log_url(@group, @badge, @log) %> <br>
      <strong>Your User Profile:</strong> 
      <%= link_to user_url(@to_user), user_url(@to_user) %> 
    </p>
    <p>
      <i>
        This email was sent automatically by the Badge List app.
        Badge List is a badge-based tool for tracking learning progress. 
        If you take no action you will not receive any further emails about this change.
      </i>
    </p>
  </body>
</html>